##Tools: 

Burp suites: Manipulate HTTP headers(like X-forwarded-Host) to test if a cache server can be tricked into saving bad data.
Curl: Command-line tool for checking cache status headers, cache-control, HIT,MISS.


##Blue team(defenders):
Process: Blue teams strictly configure cache servers to only store static, public files(img, css stylesheets). Explicitly forbid the caching of dynamic, sensitive data 
like login pages or payment screen and use short expiration times to prevent stale data.

End goal: To ensure cache components cannon be used to distribute maliciius code or expose user secrets.

##Read team(attackers): 
Process: In an attack called Web Cache Poisoning, the attacker sends a specially crafted HTTP request containing malicious Javascript to the website. If the server
handles it poorly and the cache stores it, the attacker successfylly "poisons" that asset for subsequent visitors.

End Goal: to execute malicous code on the browsers of unsuspecting users at scale.
